-- Polyus, MTS, Novatek, Severstal May Move: Russia Equity Preview
-- B y   H e n r y   M e y e r
-- 2011-01-28T05:00:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-01-27/polyus-mts-novatek-severstal-may-move-russia-equity-preview.html
The following companies may be
active in Russian trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses and
share prices are from the previous close in Moscow.  The 30-stock  Micex Index  added 0.3 percent to 1,751.54.  OAO Polyus Gold (PLZL RX): The country’s biggest gold
producer is scheduled to report fourth-quarter and full-year
production results. The shares fell 0.5 percent to 1,715.96
rubles.  OAO Mobile TeleSystems (MTSI RX): Russia’s largest mobile-
phone operator aims to be among the world’s largest five phone
companies, said AFK Sistema’s Chairman  Vladimir Yevtushenkov .
AFK Sistema controls Mobile TeleSystems. The stock fell 1.1
percent to 252.87 rubles.  OAO Novatek (NOTK RX): Russia’s second-biggest gas producer
is selling $600 million of five-year bonds and $650 million of
10-year bonds yielding 312.5 basis points over mid-swaps,
according to a banker with knowledge of the sale. The shares
fell 1.1 percent to 318.86 rubles.  Severstal (CHMF RX):  Russia ’s largest steelmaker didn’t
violate competition rules over its planned price increases for
carmaker OAO AvtoVAZ, the Federal Anti-Monopoly Service said.
The shares fell 0.4 percent to 561.42 rubles.  To contact the reporter on this story:
